  1. Factor Analysis Principle Component Analysis(PCA) . <- prcomp(data.frame)

Get eigen values and vectors to aquire information of mainly contributing factors . <- eigen(corr(data.frame))

Use Factanal method. . <- factanal(data.frame, factors= N, rotation=varimax) #rotation method? . concept of loadings and scores.

loadings<- result$loadings
dim(loadings)
[1] 6 3
dim(subject)
[1] 10  6
fapp_sci<- numeric()
fsoc_sci<- numeric()
fnat_sci<- numeric()
for ( i in 1:nrow(subject)){ #10 samples
  fs1_sum<- 0;fs2_sum<-0;fs3_sum<-0 # variable where each factor projection will be stored.
  
  for (j in 1:ncol(subject)){ # 6 subjects
    fs1_sum<-fs1_sum + (loadings[j,1] * subject[i, j])
    fs2_sum<- fs2_sum + (loadings[j, 2] * subject[i, j])
    fs3_sum<- fs3_sum + (loadings[j, 3] * subject[i, j])
  }
  
  fapp_sci[i]<- fs1_sum
  fsoc_sci[i]<- fs2_sum
  fnat_sci[i]<- fs3_sum
}
